[WhiteElo "2102"]
[BlackElo "2075"]
[Termination "JhonVivs won by checkmate"]
[ECO "B23"]
[EndTime "4:46:00 GMT+0000"]
[Link "https://www.chess.com/game/live/128062191681"]

1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. Nf3 d6 4. d4 cxd4 5. Nxd4 Nf6 6. Be2 e6 7. Be3 Be7 8. Qd2
O-O 9. O-O Qc7 10. Ndb5 Qb8 11. Rad1 Rd8 12. Bf4 e5 13. Bg5 Be6 14. f4 a6 15. f5
axb5 16. fxe6 fxe6 17. Bxb5 Nd4 18. Bxf6 Bxf6 19. Bc4 Qc7 20. Qd3 Rac8 21. Bb3
Qc5 22. Kh1 b5 23. Qh3 Re8 24. Qg4 Kf7 25. Qh5+ Kg8 26. Rd3 b4 27. Rh3 bxc3 28.
Rxf6 gxf6 29. Qxh7+ Kf8 30. Qh8+ Ke7 31. Rh7+ Kd8 32. Qxf6+ Re7 33. Qxe7# 1-0

The Game is about when Opponent gives a Piece move you must encounter with a Piece move and not Pawn move with b4 which is a blunder.
N*b3 was necessary


